# 🔴 CRITICAL — Will crash or cause data loss

**#1 — `refundFunds` never actually credits the buyer's wallet**
`EscrowService.refundFunds()` records a `REFUND` transaction but never calls `wallet.update` to increment the balance. The buyer's money disappears. `DisputesService.resolveDispute()` does this correctly — `refundFunds` does not.

**#2 — `JwtAuthGuard` in `auth/guards/` is a Strategy, not a Guard**
`auth/guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts` extends `PassportStrategy(Strategy)` instead of `AuthGuard('jwt')`. It has no `canActivate` method. Any route decorated with `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` importing from this file will crash at runtime.

**#3 — `GET /sellers/me` always 404s — breaks every seller dashboard**
`sellers.controller.ts` only has `GET /sellers/me/profile`, not `GET /sellers/me`. The frontend calls `/sellers/me`. Additionally, route ordering places `GET :id` before `GET me/profile`, so `"me"` gets passed as a seller ID to a DB query that returns null → `NotFoundException`. Every seller dashboard fails to load.

**#4 — `MANUAL` payment provider crashes Prisma**
`AdminService.markOrderPaid()` sets `provider: 'MANUAL' as any`. `PaymentProvider` enum has no `MANUAL` member. This will throw a Prisma validation error at runtime.

**#5 — Admin password hardcoded and publicly exposed**
`AdminPasswordGuard` falls back to `'Fadekemi123@'` and the same value is in `.env.example`. Anyone who clones the repo has a working admin password.

**#6 — WebSocket notifications auth bypass**
The notifications gateway authenticates by having the client send its own `userId` string with no JWT verification. Any client can subscribe to any other user's real-time notifications by sending any `userId`. Same issue in `MessagesGateway`.

**#7 — `prisma db push --accept-data-loss` runs on every server startup**
`main.ts` executes this on boot. In a multi-instance deployment (e.g., Render auto-scaling), two instances starting simultaneously with a destructive schema change could silently drop columns/tables.

