# 🟠 BROKEN FEATURES / MISSING IMPLEMENTATIONS

**#8 — No withdrawal requests are ever created in the DB**
`WalletService.withdraw()` debits the wallet and records a wallet transaction but never calls `withdrawalRequests.create`. The admin withdrawal approval flow has nothing to approve — the creation path is missing entirely.

**#9 — `reviews/seller/:id` route doesn't exist**
`getSellerReviews()` exists in the service but is never exposed via a controller endpoint. The seller dashboard calls this and gets 404s.

**#10 — `processRefund` is a TODO with no real provider call**
It only marks the payment as `REFUNDED` in the DB but never calls Flutterwave or Paymento to actually refund the money.

**#11 — `SupportTickets` has no message/response model**
There's no way for support agents to reply to tickets. The model has status/assignment endpoints but no conversation thread.

**#12 — `CurrencyService` (backend) is registered in no module**
`common/services/currency.service.ts` is dead code — never provided anywhere.

**#13 — `WalletsModule` is a dead duplicate of `WalletModule`**
`wallets.module.ts` registers identical routes and is never imported. But `wallet/index.ts` re-exports from it, which can cause confusing import resolution.

**#14 — `support.service.ts` never notifies user on ticket resolution**
Has a `// TODO: Send notification to user` comment and nothing else.

**#15 — Duplicate `RegisterDto` — two versions with different validation**
`login.dto.ts` exports a `RegisterDto` with `@IsEmail()` and `@MinLength(8)`. `register.dto.ts` exports a different one without those validators. The controller uses the one from `login.dto.ts`; the barrel export uses `register.dto.ts`. Conflicting types.

**#16 — `sellers.controller.ts` PATCH doesn't verify ownership**
`updateSeller(@Param('id') sellerId, @CurrentUserId() _userId)` — `_userId` is unused. Any authenticated user can update any seller's profile.

**#17 — `markDelivered` doesn't check `acceptedAt`**
A seller can mark an order delivered without ever accepting it, bypassing the 1-hour delivery timer entirely.

**#18 — `confirmDelivery` overwrites `paidAt`**
Sets `paidAt: new Date()` at delivery confirmation time. This stomps over the original payment timestamp.

**#19 — Nested `rewardsService.creditCoins()` inside a Prisma transaction**
`creditCoins` opens its own `$transaction` inside the outer one in `confirmDelivery`. Nested Prisma transactions can deadlock. Should be called after the outer transaction resolves.

