# 🟡 TYPE ERRORS, SCHEMA MISMATCHES & CONFIG

**#20 — `listings/index.ts` exports from `./dto/search.dto` which doesn't exist**
The file is `search-listing.dto.ts`. This barrel export will fail at compile time.

**#21 — `checkout-content.tsx` calls `useCurrency()` after conditional early returns**
React hook called conditionally. Will throw "Rendered more hooks than during the previous render" in the browser.

**#22 — `auth/callback/page.tsx` reads user data from URL hash — open redirect risk**
`firstName`, `lastName`, `role`, `email` are all read directly from the URL fragment with no validation. A crafted redirect URL can inject attacker-controlled user data.

**#23 — `JwtStrategy` has no fallback for `JWT_SECRET`**
`configService.get('JWT_SECRET')` returns `undefined` if the env var is missing. The app module has a fallback secret but the Passport strategy doesn't, causing JWT verification to fail inconsistently.

**#24 — `DIRECT_URL` missing from `.env.example`**
Prisma `schema.prisma` requires `DIRECT_URL` (needed for Supabase connection pooling) but it's not documented in `.env.example`. New devs won't know to set it.

**#25 — `create-listing.dto.ts` has `skins`/`characters` typed as `@IsNumber()` but schema is `Json?`**
The DTO has `skins?: number` but the DB column is a JSON array of objects. These fields aren't even mapped in `createListing`, making them stale dead code with wrong types.

**#26 — `updateListing` uses `|| ` fallback — can't update a price to `0`**
```ts
price: dto.price || listing.price
```
A falsy value (like `0` or empty string) silently keeps the old value. Should use `dto.price !== undefined`.

**#27 — `AffiliateService` loses decimal precision**
Uses `Number(wallet.balance) + rewardAmount` instead of Prisma `Decimal.plus()`. The rest of the codebase uses `Decimal` arithmetic correctly.

**#28 — Currency rates are hardcoded and inconsistent**
Frontend uses NGN rate of `1615`, backend uses `1600`. No live rate fetching. Prices will drift from real-world values indefinitely.

**#29 — `PaginationDto.skip` has no decorators and is dead**
`skip` has no `@IsOptional()` or `@IsNumber()`. Sending `?skip=foo` bypasses validation. The field isn't even used — `offset` (a getter) is used instead.

**#30 — `POST /payments/webhook/flutterwave` has no signature verification**
The `verif-hash` header from Flutterwave is never checked. Security is maintained via the verify-transaction call, but rejecting forged webhooks early is standard practice.

**#31 — Rate limiter (100 req/min) applies to all routes including public GET /listings**
Shared office IPs or proxied users will be rate-limited on basic browsing. Public GET routes should be exempted or have a higher limit.

**#32 — `LoggingInterceptor` uses `console.log` instead of NestJS `Logger`**
Bypasses the structured NestJS logger. Inconsistent with the rest of the codebase.

**#33 — `GigsModule` likely missing `OrdersModule` import**
`GigsService` references `OrdersService`. If `OrdersModule` isn't imported in `GigsModule`, startup will throw.

